data.name: qstn_opmode.ToolTip
data.value:
Details of supported operating modes:
Automatic Mode: ADC readings shall be started based on the timing parameters configured. Relevant Timing Parameters: T1 to T10.
Continuous mode: The PSoC shall continuously sample ONE channel of data. The Start and Stop buttons shall help to control the flow.
External Stimulation: Stimulation (VDAC) pulses shall begin on receiving a trigger pulse on a PSoC GPIO pin. The amplitude, phases, and duration shall be defined according to the standard stimulation timing parameters. There will be only one pulse VDAC waveform per trigger pulse. ADC will not be in use. Relevant Timing Parameters: T5-T7
External Recording: ADC reading shall be started based on an external trigger pulse received on a PSoC GPIO pin. On getting a trigger, T10 ms of data (per channel) shall be sampled and sent to remote PC using wireless module. Only one “chunk” of data per channel shall be sent to PC. VDAC Stimulation will not be in use. Relevant Timing Parameters: T10, Irrelevant Timing Parameters: T1-T9
Look-Ahead External: The PSoC shall continuously sample ONE channel of data. Sampled data shall be placed into a circular buffer. On receiving an external trigger pulse on a GPIO pin, T10 milliseconds of data will be sent to the PC. However, data to be sent will include T9 ms of data that occurred before the external trigger and T10-T9 ms of data that occurred after the trigger pulse for a total duration of T10 ms. VDAC stimulation will not be in use. Relevant Timing Parameters: T9 and T10, Irrelevant Timing Parameters: T1-T8
